<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3421] rebar as dependency instead of bundling (was:  rebar fails if PWD contains Unicode)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3421</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I build erlang support in a directory which contains Unicode characters I get following error:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;make[3]: &#1074;&#1093;&#1086;&#1076; &#1074; &#1082;&#1072;&#1090;&#1072;&#1083;&#1086;&#1075; &#171;/home/lyokha/&#1047;&#1072;&#1075;&#1088;&#1091;&#1079;&#1082;&#1080;/thrift-0.9.3/lib/erl&#187;
./rebar get-deps
==&amp;gt; erl (get-deps)
Uncaught error in rebar_core: {&apos;EXIT&apos;,
                               {badarg,
                                [{re,split,
                                  [[80,87,68,61,47,104,111,109,101,47,108,121,
                                    111,107,104,97,47,1047,1072,1075,1088,
                                    1091,1079,1082,1080,47,116,104,114,105,
                                    102,116,45,48,46,57,46,51,47,108,105,98,
                                    47,101,114,108],
                                   &quot;=&quot;,
                                   [{return,list},{parts,2}]],
                                  [{file,&quot;re.erl&quot;},{line,170}]},
                                 {rebar_port_compiler,&apos;-os_env/0-lc$^0/1-0-&apos;,
                                  1,[]},
                                 {rebar_port_compiler,&apos;-os_env/0-lc$^0/1-0-&apos;,
                                  1,[]},
                                 {rebar_port_compiler,os_env,0,[]},
                                 {rebar_port_compiler,setup_env,1,[]},
                                 {rebar_core,&apos;-setup_envs/2-lc$^0/1-0-&apos;,2,[]},
                                 {rebar_core,setup_envs,2,[]},
                                 {rebar_core,execute,4,[]}]}}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reason of this is that thrift uses very old prebuilt rebar:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;rebar version: 2 date: 20110618_061440 vcs: git 3e41385
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It does not include unicode option for &lt;em&gt;re:split&lt;/em&gt;. Newer rebar (since 20 Nov 2012 &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/rebar/rebar/commit/61c353dcfdafb87107cc5472709d229c26a8cb6c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/rebar/rebar/commit/61c353dcfdafb87107cc5472709d229c26a8cb6c&lt;/a&gt; revision) has this option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Workaround&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;install erlang-rebar package in the system and replace all &lt;em&gt;./rebar&lt;/em&gt; entries with &lt;em&gt;rebar&lt;/em&gt; in &lt;em&gt;lib/erl/Makefile.am&lt;/em&gt; (before running ./configure) or in &lt;em&gt;lib/erl/Makefile&lt;/em&gt; (after running ./configure).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Better fix&lt;/b&gt; would be inclusion of a newer prebuilt rebar or create dependency on a system rebar.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
